                Jessica is of mixed Filipina ancestry and grew up in Pennsylvania as the oldest of six. She became a first-generation college student, studying social science at her local community college and going on to complete a Bachelor of Arts at the California Institute of Integral Studies. In 2015, Jessica enrolled in a work exchange program that brought her to Lahaina on the island of Maui. Jessica has spent the majority of her career working in various nonprofit services, including public libraries, the Head Start program, affordable housing, and financial literacy.
